The paper focuses on developing an automatic segmentation method for the spine using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning algorithms for medical image analysis also makes it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of the segmentation method for diagnosing spine conditions and performing surgery with computer-assisted surgery systems, which relates to the medical imaging (cs.MED) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
